column11: Cerber is a ransomware family that encrypts documents, photos, databases and other important files. Historically, this malware would replace files with encrypted versions and add the file extension ".cerber," although in more recent campaigns, other file extensions are used.
column12: Futher investigation should be taken upon being alerted.
